  "description": "All orders from 2025 have been shipped. Stock from 2026 production is available now and ships in 3-5 days. Bring real-time video effects to your live shows and motion design projects with a compact instrument built for performance and animation. Load programs that blur, enhance, displace, glitch, colorize, key, posterize, and crush both digital and analog signals into entirely new visual dimensions. Tweak every parameter with dedicated hardware controls, or push the instrument further by modulating any setting with audio signals and control voltages from other synthesizers. At its core, Videomancer runs on a unique FPGA architecture that processes video with programmable digital logic. Unlike GPU-based platforms or software plug-ins, this approach delivers ultra-low-latency audio-visualization and responsive motion control. The low-level flexibility of FPGAs makes Videomancer especially well-suited for recreating the character of classic broadcast effects and video gear from the 1980s and 1990s—while opening new possibilities for modern workflows. Comprehensive I/O – HDMI, Composite, Component YPbPr, Component RGB, and 1V DC-coupled RGB. Supports seamless HDMI-to-analog and analog-to-HDMI conversion. Broad Format Support – Compatible with NTSC, PAL, 240p, 288p, 480p, 576p, 720p50/59.94/60, 1080i50/59.94/60, and 1080p23.98/24/25/29.97/30. High-Fidelity Processing – 10-bit color depth across both analog and digital streams for precise colorization and proc-amp effects. Creative Range – From professional-grade processing to destructive glitch, noise, and bit-reduction programs. External Control – Full MIDI control map via TRS Type A jacks plus four Audio/CV inputs supporting both line-level and modular signals. Performance-Ready Presets – Save and recall complete system states for shows and projects, with automatic state retention after power-up. Expandable & Updatable – Update firmware with a single USB cable (no special software required) and use the built-in microSD slot for extra programs and user data. Studio & Stage Ready – Powered by standard 12V DC barrel supply (CCTV/broadcast compatible) in a rugged powder-coated steel enclosure with industrial screen printing. Device Dimensions (in): 9.22 / 7.01 / 2.97 Device Dimensions (mm): 234.2 / 178.1 / 75.44 Included Items: Videomancer Device, 12V DC Wall Adapter with International Plugs Kit, Mystical Velvet Pouch, 12-Sided Oracular Polyhedron, Videomancer Vinyl Sticker, Star Stickers, Fortune Telling Fish, Connectors & Controls Card. Learn more about Videomancer on our documentation website! Or download firmware binaries from our public repository ."
}
